Created 1.4.1985 out of the parish of Toton & Eling. See also 
    Table 2, note (h).

On 30.9.1895 the part in Wiltshire became 
    the separate parish of East Bramshaw, so that thereafer Bramshaw was 
    entirely 
    in Hampshire. See also Table 2, notes (e) and (h).

Created 30.9.1894 out of the parish of Eling. Abolished 
    1.10.1934 and divided between the parishes of Denny Lodge and Eling.

Created 30.9.1894 out of the parish of Eling. See also Table 2, 
    note (h).

Renamed 1.8.1984 to become the parish of Hythe & Dibden. See also 
    Table 2, note (d).

    Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Bramshaw.

Renamed 1.4.1974 to become the parish of Totton & Eling. See also 
    Table 2, note (c).

Created 1.4.1979 out of the New Forest unparished area. See 
    also Table 2, note (h).

Created 1.8.1984 by renaming the parish of Dibden. See also Table 
    2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the New Forest unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (b).

Created 1.4.1979 out of the New Forest unparished area. See 
    also Table 2, note (h).

Created 30.9.1894 out of the parish of Eling. See also Table 2, 
    notes (d) and (h).

Created 30.9.1894 out of the parish of Eling. See also Table 2, 
    note (h).

    and divided between the parishes of Hordle,
